Overload.descr: ACOS returns the angle, in radians, whose cosine is x.
This function creates a new client on the server.
This function lets you pre-define cube interdependencies to avoid lock contention problems during normal system use.
This function creates a new user group on the server.
This TurboIntegrator function filters InfoCube data as it is pulled into TM1.
This function deletes an ASCII file.
This function writes a comma-delimited record to an ASCII file.
ASIN returns the angle, in radians, whose sine is x.
This function assigns a password to an existing client on a server.
This function assigns an existing client on a server to an existing user group.
ATAN returns the angle, in radians, whose tangent is x. The result is between -pi/2 and +pi/2.
This function deletes an element attribute from the TM1 database.
This function creates a new element attribute for a dimension. The function can create a string, numeric, or alias attribute.
ATTRN returns a numeric attribute for a specified element of a dimension.
This function assigns a value to a numeric element attribute.
This function assigns a value to a string element attribute.
ATTRS returns a string attribute for a specified element of a dimension.
This function instructs the server to exit batch update mode.

This TurboIntegrator function is identical to the BatchUpdateFinish function with the following exception: If a process calls BatchUpdateFinishWait, but is unable to secure a cube write lock to commit changes, the process will wait until the lock becomes available and then commit changes. Data changes applied in the process are not rolled back and the process is not re-executed.
CAPIT applies initial capitalization to every word in a string.
This function retrieves a value from a numeric cube cell.
This function retrieves a value from a string cube cell.
This function lets you determine if a cube cell can be written to.
This function sends a numeric value to a cube cell.
This function distributes a specified value to the leaves of a consolidation proportional to existing cell values.
This function sends a string value to a cube cell.
CHAR returns the character identified by a given ASCII numeric code.
CODE returns the ASCII numeric code for a specified character within a string.
This function calculates the average value in a consolidation and returns a single value.
This function counts the value in a consolidation and returns a single value.
This function calculates the maximum value in a consolidation and returns a single value.
This function calculates the minimum value in a consolidation and returns a single value.
COS returns the cosine of an angle expressed in radians.
This clears all of the data in a cube.
This function creates a cube from specified dimensions. The order of dimensions specified in the function will be the order of dimensions in the cube definition.
Acquires a Data Reservation for the specified cube, user and tuple.
Finds existing reservations on a specific cube for all or one user.
Finds existing reservations on a specific cube that would conflict with the specified user, address and tuple.
Releases the specified Data Reservation.
Releases multiple existing Data Reservations.
This function deletes a specified TM1 cube.
Use CubeExists to determine if a specific cube exists on the server from which a TurboIntegrator process is executed.
This function returns the Boolean value of the Logging property for a specified cube.
This function reprocesses all feeders in the rules for a specified cube.
CubeSaveData() serializes a cube.
This function is used to encrypt the password for a virtual cube in the }CubeProperties cube.
This function sets the LOGGING property for a cube.
This function unloads a specified cube, along with all associated cube views, from memory.

This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the decimal separator to be used in any conversion of a string to a number or a number to a string. If you set this variable you must also set the DatasourceASCIIThousandSeparator variable.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the ASCII character to be used as a field delimiter when the DatasourceType is 'CHARACTERDELIMITED'.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the number of header rows to skip when loading.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the ASCII character used to enclose the fields of the source file when DatasourceType is 'CHARACTERDELIMITED'.

This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the thousands separator to be used in any conversion of a string to a number or a number to a string. If you set this variable you must also set the DatasourceASCIIDecimalSeparator variable.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the view to process if the DatasourceType is 'VIEW'.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the subset to process if the DatasourceType is 'SUBSET.'
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the name of the data source (.cma file, cube name, ODBC source) used by the client when creating or editing the process.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the name of the data source (.cma file, cube name, ODBC source) used by the server when executing the process.

This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the name of the database collection that contains the cubes, dimensions or other objects to which you want to connect. For Microsoft Analysis Services, this is the name of the database.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets any additional connection parameters that may be required to connect to the OLAP server.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the name of the cube from the OLAP server that you want to use as a data source.

This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the name of the hierarchy for the specific dimension you are using as a data source. You use this variable for other OLAP products, such as SAP BW, where a hierarchy is a separate object. This variable is not used with TM1 data sources.

This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the name of the location (system) where the OLAP server is running. TM1 uses this variable, but other OLAP servers do not. For TM1 , this is the location where the Admin Host is running.

This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the name of the ODBO provider that you want to use as a data source. This is the full name that is assigned by the ODBO provider manufacturer to identify their multidimensional database server. You must use the name of an ODBO provider that is installed on your server.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the client number that corresponds to the UI version on the SAP server to which you want to connect.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the language specification for the language of the SAP system to which you want to connect.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the password used to connect to the data source.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the query string to use with the data source.
This TurboIntegrator function instructs the TurboIntegrator process to ignore security information when processing an SAP datasource. This variable must be placed in the Prolog.

This TurboIntegrator local variable instructs the TurboIntegrator process to ignorecharacteristic descriptions when processing an SAP datasource, resulting in a decreased memory consumption and increased performance. This variable must be placed in the Prolog.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the type of the data source.
This TurboIntegrator local variable sets the name used to connect to the data source.
DATE returns the date string in 'yy-mm-dd' or 'yyyy-mm-dd' format for a given serial number.
DATES returns a date string, in the form 'yy-mm-dd' or 'yyyy-mm-dd', corresponding to a given year, month, and day.
DAY returns a numeric value for the day in a given date string. A date string in either YY-MM-DD or YYYY-MM-DD format.
DAYNO returns the serial date number corresponding to a given date string.
DELET returns the result of deleting a specified number of characters from a specified starting point within a string.
This function deletes a client from the server.
This function deletes a user group from the server.
This function creates a new dimension.
This function deletes all the elements in a dimension.
This function deletes a dimension from the TM1 database.
This function adds a component (child) to a consolidated element. Note that you cannot use this function in the Epilog procedure of a TurboIntegrator process.
This function deletes a component (child) from a consolidated element.
This function deletes an element from a dimension.

This function adds an element to a dimension. You can use this function to add numeric, string, or consolidated elements. Note that you cannot use this function in the Data or Epilog procedures of a TurboIntegrator process.
This function returns the principal name of an element or element alias.
Use DimensionExists to determine if a specific dimension exists.
This function sets a sort type and sense for dimension elements and for components of consolidated elements within a dimension.
DIMIX returns the index number of an element within a dimension.
DIMNM returns the element of a dimension that corresponds to the index argument.
DIMSIZ returns the number of elements within a specified dimension.
DNEXT returns the element name that follows the element specified as an argument to the function.
DNLEV returns the number levels in a dimension.

DTYPE returns information about the element type of a specified element. It returns N if the element is a numeric element, S if the element is a string element, and C if the element is a consolidated element.
ELCOMP returns the name of a child of a consolidated element in a specified dimension. If the element argument is not a consolidated element, the function returns 0.
ELCOMPN returns the number of components in a specified element.
This function retrieves the security level assigned to a specified group for a dimension element.
This function assigns a security level to a specified group for a dimension element.
ELISANC determines whether element1 is an ancestor of element2 in the specified dimension.
ELISCOMP determines whether element1 is a child of element2 in the specified dimension.
ELISPAR determines whether element1 is a parent of element2 in the specified dimension.
ELLEV returns the level of an element within a dimension.
ELPAR returns the parent of an element in a specified dimension.
ELPARN returns the number of parents of an element in a specified dimension.
This is contained within an IF statement block and executes if the condition is true.
ELWEIGHT returns the weight of a child in a consolidated element.
This function executes a command line during a process. You can use ExecuteCommand to run a desktop application, but not a service.
This function lets you execute a TurboIntegrator process from within another process.
EXP returns the natural anti-log of a number.

This function 'expands' TurboIntegrator variable names, enclosed in % signs, to their values at run time. If the variable name represents a string variable, the entire variable expression must be enclosed on quotes. For example, '%V1%'.
This function determines if a specified file exists.
FILL repeats a given string as necessary to return a string of a specified length.
FV returns the value of an annuity at the time of the last payment. An annuity is a series of payments made at equal intervals of time. Payments are assumed to be made at the end of each period.

This function returns the full pathname, with trailing slash, of the directory where TurboIntegrator process error files are written. (By default, all process error log files are written to the data directory of the server on which the process resides.)

This function returns the name of the TurboIntegrator process error log file associated with a process. If the process has not yet generated an error log file, the function returns an empty (null) string.
This function returns as a string the name of the current process.

This function returns a Boolean value that indicates whether a process reads and writes data to the base data or to the user's active sandbox. The default is for processes to read and write to the base data.
INSRT inserts one string into another string at a specified insertion point.
INT returns the largest integer that is less than or equal to a specified value.
ISUND returns 1 if a specified value is undefined; otherwise it returns 0.
This function rejects a source record and places it in the error log, along with a specified error message.
LN returns the natural logarithm (base e) of a number.
LOG returns the base 10 logarithm of a positive number.
LONG returns the length of a string.
LOWER converts all upper case characters in a string to lower case.
MAX returns the largest number in a pair of values.
This TurboIntegrator global variable counts the minor errors that occur in the MetaData portion of a TurboIntegrator process. For each minor error encountered, the variable value is incremented by 1.
MIN returns the smallest number in a pair of values.

This TurboIntegrator local variable defines the number of minor errors that will be written to the TM1ProcessError.log file during process execution. If this variable is not defined in the process, the default number of minor errors written to the log file is 1000.
MOD returns the remainder of dividing a number by a divisor.
MONTH returns a numeric value for the month in a given date string. A date string in either YY-MM-DD or YYYY-MM-DD format.
NOW returns the current date/time value in serial number format.
This function converts a number to a string, using the decimal separator for the current user locale. (In Windows, the decimal separator is a Regional Options setting.)
This function converts a number to a string, using the passed string format, decimal separator, and thousands separator.
NUMBR converts a string to a number.
Use this function to declare a numeric global variable.
Use this function to declare a numeric user variable.
This function closes a connection to an ODBC data source.
This function opens an ODBC data source for output.
This function opens an ODBC data source for output specifying that the connection should be opened as a Unicode connection.
This function executes an SQL update query against an open ODBC data source.

riable instructs TurboIntegrator to skip to the next record when a minor error is encountered while processing a record. This variable is useful in scenarios where a single bad field/value in a record causes multiple minor errors.

PAYMT returns the payment amount of an annuity based on a given initial value or principal, an interest rate, and a number of periods. An annuity is a series of payments made at equal intervals of time.
This TurboIntegrator global variable stores the exit status of the most recently executed TurboIntegrator process.
This TurboIntegrator global variable counts the minor errors that occur in the Prolog portion of a TurboIntegrator process. For each minor error encountered, the variable value is incremented by 1.
This function publishes a named private view on the server.
PV returns the initial or principal value of an annuity.
RAND generates a random number that is uniformly distributed between 0 and 1. The random number generator is seeded when TM1 is loaded.

This function updates the MDX hierarchies in a server without requiring you to restart the server. Use this function after configuring or editing the custom named hierarchy levels for a dimension in the }HierarchyProperties control cube. Leave parameter blank to update all dimensions.
This function removes a specified client from a user group.
ROUND rounds a given number to the nearest integer. Rounding can be done in a variety of valid ways.
ROUNDP rounds a given number at a specified decimal precision.
This function creates a TM1 rule for a specified cube from a text file.

SCAN returns a number indicating the starting location of the first occurrence of a specified substring within a given string. If the substring does not occur in the given string, the function returns zero.

This function returns the name of the executing user's active sandbox. If the user has no active sandbox, an empty string is returned. Because chores run in the context of a special admin user, and can have no active sandbox, this function will always return an empty string when executed via a chore.

This function sets the active sandbox of the executing user. An empty string is used to clear the executing user's active sandbox. This function will throw an error if the executing user does not own a sandbox with the passed name. Because chores run in the context of a special admin user, and can have no active sandbox, this function will always throw an error when executed via a chore.
ServerSandboxesDelete allows administrators to discard user sandboxes that match certain criteria.

Use this function to turn on (or off) more verbose reporting of messages to the Tm1s.log file. This function is best used as an aid to debugging chores in which several processes call one another through use of the ExecuteProcess function. Passing a zero value turns off the output of these messages, passing a non-zero value enables the output of more verbose messages. By default this flag is off.

The SetInputCharacterSet function lets you specify the character set used in a TurboIntegrator data source. If the proper converters are present on the machine hosting the server, the input file will be converted to the Unicode character set required by TM1.
This function sets whether the ODBC interface should use the Unicode 'wide' functions or the regular single-byte character functions.
The SetOutputCharacterSet function lets you specify the character set to be used when writing to a text file with the TextOutput function.
This function controls whether a process reads and writes cube data to the base data or to the user's active sandbox. The default is for processes to read and write to the base data.
SIGN determines if a number is positive, negative, or zero. The function returns 1 if the number is positive, -1 if the number is negative, and 0 if the number is zero.
SIN returns the sine of a given angle.
SQRT returns the square root of a given value.
STR converts a number to a string.
Use this function to define a string global variable.
Use this function to define a string user variable.
This function converts a string to a number, using the decimal separator for the current user locale. (In Windows, the decimal separator is a Regional Options setting.)
This function converts a string to a number, using the passed decimal separator and thousands separator.
This function sets the alias attribute to be used in a subset. SubsetAliasSet returns 1 if successful, 0 otherwise.
This function creates an empty public subset of a specified dimension.
This function creates a public subset based on a passed MDX expression.
This function deletes all elements from a public subset.
This function deletes a subset from the TM1 database.
This function deletes an element from a subset.
This function adds an element to an existing subset.
Use SubsetExists to determine if a specific public subset exists.

This function sets the Expand Above property for a subset. When this property is set to TRUE, children of a consolidation are displayed above the consolidation when the consolidation displays on a row, and to the left of the consolidation when the consolidation displays on a column.

This function applies an existing display style to a named subset. Display styles are defined for specific elements. If you apply an existing display style to a subset that includes elements that are not included in the display style, no formatting is applied to those elements.
This function returns the name of the element at a specified index location within a given subset.
This function returns the number of elements in a subset.
This function sets a subset to use all elements of the parent dimension.
SUBST returns a substring of a given string.

This function can be used in a TurboIntegrator script to force serial execution of a designated set of TurboIntegrator processes. It is recommended (but not enforced) that synchronized() calls be the first statements of a TurboIntegrator process.
TABDIM returns the dimension name that corresponds to the index argument.
TAN returns the tangent of a given angle.
This function writes a comma-delimited record to a text file.
TIME returns a string, in HH:MM format, representing the system time on the TM1 server.
TIMST returns a formatted date/time string.
TIMVL returns the numeric value of a component (year, month, etc.) of a date/time value.

AutoComplete.KeyWord: <Overload retVal="String" descr="This function returns a string giving the current TM1 Client. When executed in a process that the user is running directly, it will return the user's TM1 client name. When executed in a chore that the user runs directly, it will also return the user's TM1 client name. If run from a scheduled chore, it will return a name in the form R*, for example, R*UpdateRegionDimension.">

Overload.descr: TODAY returns the current date in yy-mm-dd format.
TRIM returns the result of trimming any leading and trailing blanks from a string.
UNDEF returns the undefined value. This function can be used to prevent datafrom being stored in a cube based on a logical test.
UPPER converts a text string to upper case.
When the DatasourceType is 'VIEW', this TurboIntegrator local variable determines whether the current cell should be treated as a string or a numeric value.
This function sets a column dimension for a TM1 view.
This function suppresses or enables the display of columns containing only zero values in a TM1 cube view.
This function constructs, pre-calculates, and stores a stargate view in memory on a server.
This function creates an empty view of a specified cube.
This function deletes a view from the TM1 database.
Use ViewExists to determine if a specific public view exists.
This function sets an option to include/exclude consolidated values in a view extract. A view extract is a TM1 view exported as an ASCII comma-delimited (.cma) file.
This function sets an option to include/exclude rule-calculated values in a view extract. A view extract is a TM1 view exported as an ASCII comma-delimited (.cma) file.
This function sets an option to include/exclude zero values in a view extract. A view extract is a TM1 view exported as an ASCII comma-delimited (.cma) file.
This function sets a row dimension for a TM1 view.
This function suppresses or enables the display of rows containing only zero values in a TM1 cube view.
This function assigns a named subset to a cube view.
This function suppresses or enables the display of all rows and columns containing only zero values in a TM1 cube view.
This function sets a title dimension for a TM1 view.
This function sets a title element for a TM1 view. ViewTitleElementSet is used in conjunction with the ViewTitleDimensionSet function.
This function sets all data points in a view to zero.
This function lets you use wildcard characters to search for files in a specified directory.
YEAR returns a numeric value for the year in a given date string.
ACOS returns the angle, in radians, whose cosine is x.

LOG returns the base 10 logarithm of a positive number.
LONG returns the length of a string.
LOWER converts all upper case characters in a string to lower case.
MAX returns the largest number in a pair of values.
This TurboIntegrator global variable counts the minor errors that occur in the MetaData portion of a TurboIntegrator process. For each minor error encountered, the variable value is incremented by 1.
MIN returns the smallest number in a pair of values.

This TurboIntegrator local variable defines the number of minor errors that will be written to the TM1ProcessError.log file during process execution. If this variable is not defined in the process, the default number of minor errors written to the log file is 1000.
MOD returns the remainder of dividing a number by a divisor.
MONTH returns a numeric value for the month in a given date string. A date string in either YY-MM-DD or YYYY-MM-DD format.
NOW returns the current date/time value in serial number format.
This function converts a number to a string, using the decimal separator for the current user locale. (In Windows, the decimal separator is a Regional Options setting.)
This function converts a number to a string, using the passed string format, decimal separator, and thousands separator.
NUMBR converts a string to a number.
Use this function to declare a numeric global variable.
Use this function to declare a numeric user variable.
This function closes a connection to an ODBC data source.
This function opens an ODBC data source for output.
This function opens an ODBC data source for output specifying that the connection should be opened as a Unicode connection.
This function executes an SQL update query against an open ODBC data source.

riable instructs TurboIntegrator to skip to the next record when a minor error is encountered while processing a record. This variable is useful in scenarios where a single bad field/value in a record causes multiple minor errors.

PAYMT returns the payment amount of an annuity based on a given initial value or principal, an interest rate, and a number of periods. An annuity is a series of payments made at equal intervals of time.
This TurboIntegrator global variable stores the exit status of the most recently executed TurboIntegrator process.
This TurboIntegrator global variable counts the minor errors that occur in the Prolog portion of a TurboIntegrator process. For each minor error encountered, the variable value is incremented by 1.
This function publishes a named private view on the server.
PV returns the initial or principal value of an annuity.
RAND generates a random number that is uniformly distributed between 0 and 1. The random number generator is seeded when TM1 is loaded.

This function updates the MDX hierarchies in a server without requiring you to restart the server. Use this function after configuring or editing the custom named hierarchy levels for a dimension in the }HierarchyProperties control cube. Leave parameter blank to update all dimensions.
This function removes a specified client from a user group.
ROUND rounds a given number to the nearest integer. Rounding can be done in a variety of valid ways.
ROUNDP rounds a given number at a specified decimal precision.
This function creates a TM1 rule for a specified cube from a text file.

SCAN returns a number indicating the starting location of the first occurrence of a specified substring within a given string. If the substring does not occur in the given string, the function returns zero.

This function returns the name of the executing user's active sandbox. If the user has no active sandbox, an empty string is returned. Because chores run in the context of a special admin user, and can have no active sandbox, this function will always return an empty string when executed via a chore.

This function sets the active sandbox of the executing user. An empty string is used to clear the executing user's active sandbox. This function will throw an error if the executing user does not own a sandbox with the passed name. Because chores run in the context of a special admin user, and can have no active sandbox, this function will always throw an error when executed via a chore.
ServerSandboxesDelete allows administrators to discard user sandboxes that match certain criteria.

Use this function to turn on (or off) more verbose reporting of messages to the Tm1s.log file. This function is best used as an aid to debugging chores in which several processes call one another through use of the ExecuteProcess function. Passing a zero value turns off the output of these messages, passing a non-zero value enables the output of more verbose messages. By default this flag is off.

The SetInputCharacterSet function lets you specify the character set used in a TurboIntegrator data source. If the proper converters are present on the machine hosting the server, the input file will be converted to the Unicode character set required by TM1.
This function sets whether the ODBC interface should use the Unicode 'wide' functions or the regular single-byte character functions.
The SetOutputCharacterSet function lets you specify the character set to be used when writing to a text file with the TextOutput function.
This function controls whether a process reads and writes cube data to the base data or to the user's active sandbox. The default is for processes to read and write to the base data.
SIGN determines if a number is positive, negative, or zero. The function returns 1 if the number is positive, -1 if the number is negative, and 0 if the number is zero.
SIN returns the sine of a given angle.
SQRT returns the square root of a given value.
STR converts a number to a string.
Use this function to define a string global variable.
Use this function to define a string user variable.
This function converts a string to a number, using the decimal separator for the current user locale. (In Windows, the decimal separator is a Regional Options setting.)
This function converts a string to a number, using the passed decimal separator and thousands separator.
This function sets the alias attribute to be used in a subset. SubsetAliasSet returns 1 if successful, 0 otherwise.
This function creates an empty public subset of a specified dimension.
This function creates a public subset based on a passed MDX expression.
This function deletes all elements from a public subset.
This function deletes a subset from the TM1 database.
This function deletes an element from a subset.
This function adds an element to an existing subset.
Use SubsetExists to determine if a specific public subset exists.

This function sets the Expand Above property for a subset. When this property is set to TRUE, children of a consolidation are displayed above the consolidation when the consolidation displays on a row, and to the left of the consolidation when the consolidation displays on a column.

This function applies an existing display style to a named subset. Display styles are defined for specific elements. If you apply an existing display style to a subset that includes elements that are not included in the display style, no formatting is applied to those elements.
This function returns the name of the element at a specified index location within a given subset.
This function returns the number of elements in a subset.
This function sets a subset to use all elements of the parent dimension.
SUBST returns a substring of a given string.

This function can be used in a TurboIntegrator script to force serial execution of a designated set of TurboIntegrator processes. It is recommended (but not enforced) that synchronized() calls be the first statements of a TurboIntegrator process.
TABDIM returns the dimension name that corresponds to the index argument.
TAN returns the tangent of a given angle.
This function writes a comma-delimited record to a text file.
TIME returns a string, in HH:MM format, representing the system time on the TM1 server.
TIMST returns a formatted date/time string.
TIMVL returns the numeric value of a component (year, month, etc.) of a date/time value.

AutoComplete.KeyWord: <Overload retVal="String" descr="This function returns a string giving the current TM1 Client. When executed in a process that the user is running directly, it will return the user's TM1 client name. When executed in a chore that the user runs directly, it will also return the user's TM1 client name. If run from a scheduled chore, it will return a name in the form R*, for example, R*UpdateRegionDimension.">

Overload.descr: TODAY returns the current date in yy-mm-dd format.
TRIM returns the result of trimming any leading and trailing blanks from a string.
UNDEF returns the undefined value. This function can be used to prevent datafrom being stored in a cube based on a logical test.
UPPER converts a text string to upper case.
When the DatasourceType is 'VIEW', this TurboIntegrator local variable determines whether the current cell should be treated as a string or a numeric value.
This function sets a column dimension for a TM1 view.
This function suppresses or enables the display of columns containing only zero values in a TM1 cube view.
This function constructs, pre-calculates, and stores a stargate view in memory on a server.
This function creates an empty view of a specified cube.
This function deletes a view from the TM1 database.
Use ViewExists to determine if a specific public view exists.
This function sets an option to include/exclude consolidated values in a view extract. A view extract is a TM1 view exported as an ASCII comma-delimited (.cma) file.
This function sets an option to include/exclude rule-calculated values in a view extract. A view extract is a TM1 view exported as an ASCII comma-delimited (.cma) file.
This function sets an option to include/exclude zero values in a view extract. A view extract is a TM1 view exported as an ASCII comma-delimited (.cma) file.
This function sets a row dimension for a TM1 view.
This function suppresses or enables the display of rows containing only zero values in a TM1 cube view.
This function assigns a named subset to a cube view.
This function suppresses or enables the display of all rows and columns containing only zero values in a TM1 cube view.
This function sets a title dimension for a TM1 view.
This function sets a title element for a TM1 view. ViewTitleElementSet is used in conjunction with the ViewTitleDimensionSet function.
This function sets all data points in a view to zero.
This function lets you use wildcard characters to search for files in a specified directory.
YEAR returns a numeric value for the year in a given date string.
